  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Schedules, assigns and plans the work of carpentry factory personnel performing a variety of carpentry projects.</li>\n  <li>Plans and develops work schedules, equipment usage schedules, priority of carpentry expenditures and procedures for equipment maintenance.</li>\n  <li>Supervises carpenters to ensure safety and quality in the performance of assigned tasks.</li>\n  <li>Take measurements and calculate the size and amount of material needed.</li>\n  <li>Constructs custom cabinetry and furniture as needed; repairs or modifies furniture as needed.</li>\n  <li>Conform to an established work schedule.</li>\n  <li>Reading blueprints, drawings and sketches to fully grasp requirements</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years related experience</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal communication and problem solving skills</li>\n  <li>Good management of materials cost and stock inventory</li>\n  <li>Experience of using hand and power tools such as drills, chisels, sanders, saws and nail guns</li>\n  <li>Joinery and cabinet making skills</li>\n  <li>Able to work for long hours period or night shift</li>\n  <li>Able to work on weekends and public holidays</li>\n</ul>",
